# Step 1: Database Provisioning

1. Go to [Neon.tech](https://neon.tech) and create a new project.
2. Select PostgreSQL 16+.
3. Copy the connection string (with pooled connection if available).
4. Create a `.env` file in the `api` directory and paste the connection string.

# Essential Terminal Commands
```powershell
# Create project structure
mkdir recipe-app
cd recipe-app
mkdir api client

# Setup API environment
cd api
cat <<EOF > .env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://[user]:[password]@[host]/[dbname]?sslmode=require
JWT_SECRET=$(openssl rand -base64 32)
REFRESH_SECRET=$(openssl rand -base64 32)
PORT=3001
EOF

# Create .env.example for team reference
cat <<EOF > .env.example
DATABASE_URL=
JWT_SECRET=
REFRESH_SECRET=
PORT=3001
EOF
```

// api/.env.example
DATABASE_URL=
JWT_SECRET=
REFRESH_SECRET=
PORT=3001
